5|$|The Penal {{system of}} Japan (矯正施設) is {{operated}} by the Ministry of Justice. It {{is part of the}} criminal justice system, and is intended to resocialize, reform, and rehabilitate offenders. The ministry's Correctional Bureau administers the adult <b>prison</b> <b>system,</b> the juvenile correctional system, and three of the women's guidance homes, while the Rehabilitation Bureau operates the probation and the parole systems.|$|E
